    <note>Pi(1) Ziliang [7314] His ancestors were Xiangyang residents. His great grandfather, Rixiu [3701], moved to Shaoxing to avoid the Guangming period (880) disturbances and served in the administration of the Wuyue kingdom. His grandfather, Guangye [3703], was a member of the Wuyue state council. His father, Can [3704], first served Wuyue and then Song. Ziliang was buried in Henan, Yongan xian. Zhongrong's [3701] father (see Gongbi [1405]), Zhang(1) Kui(1)'s [250] father-in-law. Yin Zhu, WJ, 15.5a-6a. CBD, 1, 516-7.</note>
